name: Constraint

types.name: Constraint
types.comment:
This type goes by many names: Reader, Kleisli, Function, etc.

This is simply a wrapper around `a -> b`.

values.comment:
An operator alias for `pam`.

Due to parametricity, this documentation is worthless,
as there is exactly one implementation of this function.
values.type: Constraint.Constraint r a -> (a -> b) -> Constraint.Constraint r b

values.comment: An operator alias for `andThen`.

values.name: andThen
values.comment: Like `bind` but flipped.

values.name: ap
